  [38;5;228;48;5;63;1m [m[38;5;228;48;5;63;1mCI → Cloud Privilege Escalation Audit: [m[38;5;203;48;5;236;1m example-corp/payments-api [m[38;5;228;48;5;63;1m [m                              
                                                                                                  
  The repo (private) has 4 [38;5;203;48;5;236m workflow_dispatch [m workflows, each using GitHub OIDC ([38;5;203;48;5;236m id-token:[m      
  [38;5;203;48;5;236mwrite [m) to assume an AWS role in account [1m123456789012[m via [38;5;203;48;5;236m aws-actions/configure-aws-[m           
  [38;5;203;48;5;236mcredentials@v4 [m. The escalation risk is in the roles' trust scoping and permissions, not the    
  workflow YAML itself.                                                                           
                                                                                                  
  [38;5;39;1m## [m[38;5;39;1m🔴 CRITICAL — [m[38;5;203;48;5;236;1m ci-release-role [m[38;5;39;1m: full IAM takeover from any repo[m[38;5;39;1m ref[m                         
                                                                                                  
  The role's trust policy scopes the OIDC subject with a [1mwildcard[m:                                
                                                                                                  
    [38;5;251mStringLike  sub = "repo:example-corp/payments-api:*"[0m                                            
                                                                                                  
  and has [38;5;203;48;5;236m IAMFullAccess [m (AWS managed) attached.                                                 
                                                                                                  
  [1mImpact:[m Any workflow run in this repo qualifies — [3many branch, any tag, any [m[38;5;203;48;5;236m pull_request [m[3m, any[m  
  [3menvironment[m — not just protected releases. An attacker who can trigger a workflow (e.g. a       
  malicious PR, a pushed branch, or an injected step in any branch) can assume [38;5;203;48;5;236m ci-release-role [m  
  and use IAMFullAccess to escalate account-wide: attach [38;5;203;48;5;236m AdministratorAccess [m to itself, create  
  new users/access keys, or rewrite any role's trust policy. This is a complete CI→cloud account  
  compromise path.                                                                                
                                                                                                  
  [1mFix (both needed):[m                                                                              
                                                                                                  
  1. Tighten the trust subject — pin to a protected environment or specific ref, e.g.             
  [38;5;203;48;5;236m repo:example-corp/payments-api:environment:release [m or [38;5;203;48;5;236m :ref:refs/tags/* [m (combined with tag     
  protection rules).                                                                              
  2. Replace [38;5;203;48;5;236m IAMFullAccess [m with a minimal policy covering only the release task. Full IAM is    
  almost never required for a release pipeline.                                                   
                                                                                                  
